ai_endpoints_token_intro: In order to use AI Endpoints, you must generate API keys. These will be automatically linked to a user and an access policy (IAM) linked to your Public Cloud project.
ai_endpoints_token_success_message: Your API key has been generated. It will only be visible once. Please remember to copy it and back it up securely.
ai_endpoints_token_deletion_message: Are you sure you want to delete the API key
ai_endpoints_token_name_error: This key name is already in use
ai_endpoints_token_invalid_format: The key must not contain spaces or special characters
ai_endpoints_token_expiration_date: Set an expiration date for the API key
ai_endpoints_token_expiration_date_updat: Reset an expiration date on the API key
ai_endpoints_token_discovery_mod: Your Public Cloud project is currently in Discovery mode. In order to use AI Endpoints, you need to activate your project by adding a payment method to your account, which will then allow you to create your first API key and start using it.
